{"submission_id":"sub_5359aba55c509c61","run_id":"2026-06-21T20-15-18-081Z_3137823-75f6fdea_ingest_meeting-doc-190006","submitted_at":"2026-06-21T20:33:19.742Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:5359aba55c509c61f30331699721655c32f48bc7925e481a18219e818e09509f","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_190006","observation_kind":"entity","local_observation_id":"entity_meeting_doc_190006_mabstoa","target_record_id":"entity_mabstoa","label":"Manhattan and Bronx Surface Transit Operating Authority (MaBSTOA)","raw_text":"New York City Transit Authority and its subsidiary, Manhattan and Bronx Surface Transit Operating Authority (\"MaBSTOA\"), provide subway and public bus service within the five boroughs of New York City.","payload":{"entity_name":"Manhattan and Bronx Surface Transit Operating Authority","short_name":"MaBSTOA","entity_type":"subsidiary","description":"Subsidiary of New York City Transit Authority providing subway and public bus service within the five boroughs of New York City."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_190006","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_190006#p003_c0012","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_190006/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0012","text_sha256":"sha256:b5a73000a85bdddbfa761da096d19b6bf4ab05a887d3696d60371a261945d070","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_2783ee59e6de7dd2","run_id":"2026-06-21T20-15-18-081Z_3137823-75f6fdea_ingest_meeting-doc-190006","submitted_at":"2026-06-21T20:33:57.706Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:2783ee59e6de7dd2b5f7dd26a4c8887df9ab16e4add09d47ef4d3700b8dc607c","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_190006","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_190006_2025_2029_capital_program_approval","label":"2025-2029 Capital Program approval status","raw_text":"The approved 2025-2029 Capital Programs provided $68,400 in capital expenditures. The combined funding sources for the 2025-2029 MTA Capital Programs and the 2025-2029 MTA Bridges and Tunnels Capital Program, include $31,500 in Payroll Mobility Tax new revenue source (MTA Capital Lockbox), $9,700 in MTA bonds and PAYGO, $14,000 in Federal funds, $4,200 in State of New York funding, $3,000 in City of New York funding, $3,000 from additional MTA self-funding, and $3,000 in MTA Bridges and Tunnels dedicated funds.","payload":{"claim_text":"The 2025-2029 Capital Program totaling $68,400 million was originally approved by the MTA Board on September 25, 2024, subsequently disapproved by the CPRB on December 24, 2024 because fund sources had not yet been fully identified, resubmitted and approved by the MTA Board on May 28, 2025, and subsequently approved by the CPRB on June 17, 2025. Funding sources include $31,500 in Payroll Mobility Tax, $9,700 in MTA bonds and PAYGO, $14,000 in Federal funds, $4,200 in State of New York funding, $3,000 in City of New York funding, $3,000 from additional MTA self-funding, and $3,000 in MTA Bridges and Tunnels dedicated funds."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_190006","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_190006#p011_c0013","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_190006/blocks.jsonl","page_number":11,"block_id":"p011_c0013","text_sha256":"sha256:9c418b9c2feb5b82881a3c7eaf95375c3f1093ce3b1def6633544dd50f778819","text_source":"raw_text"},{"source_id":"meeting_doc_190006","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_190006#p011_c0014","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_190006/blocks.jsonl","page_number":11,"block_id":"p011_c0014","text_sha256":"sha256:abc494df0d2cf222340f2bc660a183f21edfa784827b58bd84954d7edd6fa58c","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
